A_561 - Generally when you think of the idea of a road you think of a paved car path and nothing else. Generally when you think of vegetation, you think of plants or trees and nothing else. Generally, when you think of squares, you think of paving and nothing else. I leave this advice: when you think about these concepts in your mind, regardless of the position in which they are found, it is always better to keep in mind that with some probability there could be abandoned waste in their vicinity. In this way mental health is generally much better protected. However, I recommend carrying out periodic patrols and observations of the territory with a means of transport which allows for detailed checks (not by car). In addition to this, beyond the potential presence of waste, sometimes we also had experience of the potential presence of &ldquo;other&rdquo; (animals..., etc...) abandoned...